    "updated_at": "2015-07-29T23:51:14Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "pthreads on linux at least delays the broadcast/signal until the mutex is actually released - with the advantage that we avoid the possibility of using a double-wakeup.\n\nI'd like to (at some point) ensure we use cv.wait(..., predicate) -- there exist platforms that can optimize for this by checking if predicate is true before issuing the wakeup.\n"
